<task id="058" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-C-11 — Conflict resolution implementation (Q8: user wins; agent reads timestamp; polite re-read prompt)</title>
    <status>pending</status>
    <estimated-effort>6 hours</estimated-effort>
    <phase>Phase C — Tri-directional Workspace (Pillar 6b)</phase>
    <wave>C-G2 (parallel after 6a)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>055 (update_workspace_tab handler)</dependencies>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, chat, workspace</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Wires Q8 conflict resolution end-to-end (handler refusal → agent re-read prompt → retry); behavior change to chat agent observability.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>C-G2</parallel-group>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Wire the Q8 conflict resolution semantic end-to-end so the agent gracefully handles
    stale-read refusals from `update_workspace_tab` (task 055). On `stale_read` response
    from the handler: the chat agent receives the structured refusal, observes the
    `currentTimestamp` field, re-reads the tab via the workspace snapshot in the next
    turn's system prompt (Pillar 6a wiring task 053), and re-attempts the update with
    fresh `expectedLastUserEditAt`. This task adds: (a) instruction snippet in the
    persona / system prompt assembly explaining the conflict semantic so the LLM knows
    to re-read on stale refusal; (b) telemetry counter for conflict refusals
    (`workspace.conflict_refused`) per ADR-015 (timestamp + decision only); (c)
    integration test asserting end-to-end: user edits tab, agent attempts update with
    stale expected, handler refuses, agent re-reads + re-attempts successfully.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior AI platform engineer with familiarity with SprkChatAgent + system prompt
    assembly + LLM instruction-following behavior on structured refusals.
  </role>

  <goal>
    End-to-end conflict resolution functional: user edit, agent attempt with stale
    expected → handler refuses → agent re-reads + re-attempts → succeeds. Telemetry
    counter visible in dashboard.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="chat-arch">docs/architecture/chat-architecture.md</file>
    <file purpose="chat-factory">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgentFactory.cs</file>
    <file purpose="update-handler">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/UpdateWorkspaceTabHandler.cs</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Persona instruction snippet added via persona scope row (data) not hardcoded in C# (per Pillar 1 binding).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Conflict counter telemetry: tabId + sessionId + decision + timestamp ONLY. No content.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Publish-size delta verified.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-40">User wins; agent reads timestamp; refuses on stale write with re-read prompt. No OT/CRDT.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project Q8 binding">Refusal format: structured response with `status: "stale_read"`, `currentTimestamp`, polite message. LLM consumes + decides to re-read + re-attempt.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>bff/ai-chat-conflict</topic>
    <files>
      <file>docs/architecture/chat-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/AI-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-015-ai-data-governance.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">"🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — End-to-end conflict resolution wiring."</step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">Read TASK-INDEX; confirm 055 complete.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">Read SprkChatAgentFactory + persona system prompt assembly + UpdateWorkspaceTabHandler refusal contract.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Persona Instruction Snippet">Add a system-prompt snippet to the global SYS- persona (Pillar 1) instructing the agent: "If a tab update refuses with stale_read, re-read the tab from the current workspace state in your next turn before re-attempting the update." Data-only change; no code change.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Telemetry Counter">Add `workspace.conflict_refused` counter at the handler refusal point; emit deterministic IDs only.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Integration Test">Build end-to-end test: user edits tab → agent attempts update with stale expected → handler refuses → agent re-reads + re-attempts → succeeds. Verify counter incremented.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Publish-Size + CVE">dotnet publish; vulnerable-package check.</step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL)">code-review + adr-check (ADR-013/015/029).</step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">TASK-INDEX 058 ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build + test + publish</tool>
    <tool name="pac">Update SYS- persona row with new instruction snippet</tool>
    <tool name="git">Stage + commit</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="data">SYS- persona row updated with stale-read instruction snippet</output>
    <output type="code">Telemetry counter wiring in `UpdateWorkspaceTabHandler` (if not already in task 055)</output>
    <output type="tests">tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Workspace/ConflictResolutionTests.cs (NEW)</output>
    <output type="docs">TASK-INDEX.md, current-task.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">SYS- persona contains conflict-resolution instruction snippet.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`workspace.conflict_refused` telemetry counter emits on every stale-read refusal.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Integration test passes end-to-end: stale → refuse → re-read → re-attempt → succeed.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No user content in telemetry (ADR-015).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Publish-size delta within budget.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">code-review + adr-check pass.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
